							<div class="post">My experience with standard wall switches and low voltage signals is that you will likely have a few failed switches. Sometimes the work, sometimes they don&#039;t. <br />They are usual copper contacts, often burnt or oxidised, hence don&#039;t make for a nice reliable contact at low voltage and mA level.<br />If you can run a diode, at a minimum ,through the contact, it may be better (20mA) or a load resistor.<br /><br />No good upsetting the boss :-)<br /><br />Kim</div>
